Drug: Warfarin (Anticoagulant (vitamin K antagonist; coumarin)) | Common side effects: Easy bruising
- Minor bleeding (e.g., bleeding gums, nosebleeds)
- Prolonged bleeding from cuts | Serious: Severe or life-threatening bleeding: sudden severe headache, feeling very weak or dizzy, blood in urine, bloody or tarry stools, coughing up blood, vomit like coffee grounds, heavy or abnormal vaginal bleed